{{Quote|We got spiders inbound!|Clone Captain Rex, during the [[Battle of Malastare]]|<ref name="The Zillo Beast">{{TCW|The Zillo Beast}}</ref>}}
The '''DSD1 dwarf spider droid''',<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> or simply the '''dwarf spider droid''',<ref name="Dwarf Spider Droid" /> was a model of [[battle droid]]<ref name="dwarf spider droid" /> manufactured by [[Baktoid Armor Workshop]].<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> Favored by the [[Commerce Guild]],<ref name="Dwarf Spider Droid" /> it was first used against renegade [[miner]]s in skirmishes that took place deep underground.<ref name="Join the Battle" /> The unit was also known as the '''burrowing spider droid''' for its ability to invade narrow spaces. It was armed with a powerful [[Nose-mounted laser cannon|nose-mounted]] [[laser cannon]]<ref name="SWL" /> capable of both rapid-fire and high-intensity burst.<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> It was also shown to be used as an anti-air [[weapon]], shown during the [[Battle of Teth]] and by shooting down the [[Low Altitude Assault Transport/infantry|LAAT gunship]] carrying the [[Clone Force 99|Bad Batch]], [[Cody]], [[Rex]], [[Jesse]], and [[Kix]] on [[Anaxes]]. The four legs of the droid were designed and manufactured to allow attachment and movement on vertical terrain, such as cliffs, seen during the Battle of [[Teth]], where dwarf spider droids affixed themselves to the cliff of the [[B'omarr Order Monastery]] to utilize a superior firing angle at incoming [[clone trooper]]s and [[All Terrain Tactical Enforcer|AT-TEs]].<ref name="The Clone Wars" /><ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" />

Later, the dwarf spider droid became a mainstay in the [[droid]] [[Separatist Droid Army|army]] of the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems]] against the [[Galactic Republic]] during the [[Clone Wars]].<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> Its underbelly was vulnerable to explosives, as demonstrated when [[Clone Captain]] [[Rex]] destroyed a dwarf spider droid by planting a [[thermal detonator]] on its stomach during the Battle of Teth.<ref name="The Clone Wars" /> Many were equipped with a self-destruct mechanism that, when threatened on the battlefield, would detonate.<ref name="Character Encyclopedia U&E" /> The droids saw action in the early stages of the war, including the [[Battle of Devaron]],<ref name="Cargo of Doom" /> all the way up until some of the final engagements of the war, such as the [[Battle of Anaxes]]<ref name="The Bad Batch">{{TCW|The Bad Batch (episode)}}</ref> and the [[Battle of Kashyyyk]].<ref name="ROTS">{{Film|III}}</ref>

==Characteristics==
The DSD1 dwarf [[Spider droid (disambiguation)|spider droids]] were a type of [[battle droid]]<ref name="dwarf spider droid" /> manufactured by [[Baktoid Armor Workshop]]<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> for the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems]].<ref name="Dwarf Spider Droid" /> They had [[Gender|masculine programming]],<ref name="The Clone Wars" /> [[Color|red]] [[photoreceptor]]s, and gray plating.<ref name="Attack of the Clones" /> Their photoreceptors could see into the [[infrared]] spectrum and enabled them to see in total darkness.<ref name="Join the Battle" />

Dwarf spider [[droid]]s had one [[Nose-mounted laser cannon|nose-mounted]] [[laser cannon]],<ref name="SWL" /> which could pack a punch. They relied on this powerful, centrally mounted heavy [[blaster]] [[cannon]] to blast enemy [[troop]]s, vehicles and aircraft.<ref name="Join the Battle" /> They also had a [[self-destruct mechanism]].<ref name="Character Encyclopedia U&E" /> Dwarf spider droids were equipped with two echolocation emitters and a tracing antenna.<ref name="Droid Factory" /> The droids also had the capability of climbing vertical surfaces,<ref name="The Clone Wars" /> making them ideal for guard duty and reconnaissance. The droids were programmed to be about as smart as domestic animals and, as a result, they would sometimes refuse to follow dangerous orders.<ref name="Join the Battle" /> Dwarf spider droids were 3.05 [[meter]]s wide,<ref name="Beginnings" /> and 1.98 meters (6 [[Foot|feet]], 6 inches) tall,<ref name="Join the Battle" /> when excluding their antenna.<ref name="Dwarf Spider Droid" />

